{"cursor":"15147","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n{{Infobox Union |name= Agricultural Workers' Organization |country= United\nStates of America |affiliation= Industrial Workers of the World |members=\n100,000 |full_name= |native_name= |image= |founded= April 15, 1915 |current=\n|head= |dissolved_date= |dissolved_state= |merged_into= |office= |people=\n|website= |footnotes= }}  line, Arvin, CA, 1940]]\n\nThe 'Agricultural Workers Organization' (AWO), an organization of farm workers\nthroughout the United States and Canada, was formed on April 15, 1915 in Kansas\nCity. It was supported by, and a subsidiary organization of, the Industrial\nWorkers of the World (IWW). Although the IWW had advocated the abolition of the\nwage system as an ultimate goal since its own formation ten years earlier, the\nAWO's founding convention sought rather to address immediate needs, and\nchampioned a ten hour work day, premium pay for overtime, a minimum wage, good\nfood and bedding for workers. Melvyn Dubofsky, We Shall\nBe All, Abridged Edition, University of Illinois Press, 2000, page 182. In\n1917 the organization changed names to the Agricultural Workers Industrial Union\n(AWIU) as part of a broader reorganization of IWW industrial unions.\n\nAs a member organization of the IWW, the AWO embraced a variety of tactics in\norder to organize workers. While the AWO resolved to prohibit street speaking\nand soap boxing â a common method by which the parent organization communicated\nits more radical message to workers â soapboxing was practiced by AWO delegates,\nand met with considerable success. Henry E.\nMcGucken, Memoirs of a Wobbly, Charles H. Kerr Publishing Company, 1987, page\n70. The AWO developed the roving delegate system for member sign-up and\ndues collection, which is still used by the IWW. Within two years, the AWO had\nachieved a membership of a hundred thousand. Henry E. McGucken, Memoirs of a\nWobbly, Charles H. Kerr Publishing Company, 1987, page 70-73.\n","linknr":141,"url":"Agricultural_Workers_Organization","recorded":1375072733,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Agricultural_Workers_Organization&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Agricultural_Workers_Organization&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/United_States_of_America","/wiki/Industrial_Workers_of_the_World","/wiki/File:Arvin,_Kern_County,_California._..._Close-up_of_relief_queue_on_S.R.A._pay_day._Man_in_foreground_is_._._._-_NARA_-_521652.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cd/Arvin%2C_Kern_County%2C_California._..._Close-up_of_relief_queue_on_S.R.A._pay_day._Man_in_foreground_is_._._._-_NARA_-_521652.jpg/220px-Arvin%2C_Kern_County%2C_California._..._Close-up_of_relief_queue_on_S.R.A._pay_day._Man_in_foreground_is_._._._-_NARA_-_521652.jpg","/wiki/File:Arvin,_Kern_County,_California._..._Close-up_of_relief_queue_on_S.R.A._pay_day._Man_in_foreground_is_._._._-_NARA_-_521652.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.22wmf11/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","/wiki/California_State_Relief_Administration","/wiki/Arvin,_California","/wiki/Farmworker","/wiki/United_States","/wiki/Canada","/wiki/Kansas_City,_Missouri","/wiki/Industrial_Workers_of_the_World","/wiki/Fi